{
  "stem": "2165.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used to-- like 3,000 Jews they used to grab to concentration camps, working camps, like men, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When this happened, you used to hide.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this usually took between a day and three days, and then we used to come out and get on again with the-- with our regular life.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this, I think, happened in our city three times till they declared that I have to-- we have to go and go live in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Germans-- the German Army, when they marched to Russia, exchanged-- come back from Russia-- I remember they used to have on the streets orchestras.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they gave shows for the Army by catching Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Shave their heads, beat them up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was their entertainment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Me as a child, by not wearing any marks, I could be there and watch it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The ghetto lasted from December-- like I told you-- until probably May.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I celebrated my bar mitzvah in a small, little house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was only 10 people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was two rooms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We must have lived maybe-- maybe 12 people, 14 people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Two little rooms, yeah.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, food was rationed by German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Me and my sister had a lot of stuff left over from my mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When they took my mother, we took a lot of stuff.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My older sister was engaged.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in Poland, there was a-- a habit when somebody got married, the mother used to prepare for her, you know-- bedspreads and pillow sheets and-- and we had a lot of stuff left from my mother.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Me and my sister used to sell, once in a while, some merchandise and help out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To live, because my aunt and uncle were not economically well done.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
